official_title: A bill to amend title II of the Social Security Act to provide that a woman may become entitled to full old-age insurance benefits at age 60.
subjects: Old age, survivors and disability insurance

summary.text: Provides, under title II of the Social Security Act (Old-Age, Survivors' and Disability Insurance), that a woman may become entitled to full old-age insurance benefits at age 60 (presently 62).

titles.title: A bill to amend title II of the Social Security Act to provide that a woman may become entitled to full old-age insurance benefits at age 60.
